Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Set/StrictSubSet

Synopsis Strict subset operator on set values.
Syntax Exp1 < Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 < Exp2
set[T1] set[T2] bool
Description Yields true if the value of Exp1 is a strict subset of the value of Exp2, and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>{1, 2, 3} < {1, 2, 3, 4};
bool: true
rascal>{1, 2, 3} < {1, 3, 4};
bool: false
rascal>{1, 2, 3} < {1, 2, 3};
bool: false
